# Project Structure

The codebase follows Next.js App Router conventions with a modular organization pattern.

## Key Directories

- **src/app/** - Next.js App Router pages and layouts
  - **(root)/** - Main app routes with parallel routing (@app and @login)
  - **api/** - API routes and serverless functions

- **src/components/** - Reusable React components
  - **ui/** - Low-level UI components (buttons, inputs, etc.)
  - **chat/** - Chat and messaging components
  - **messages/** - Message display and composition
  - **community/** - Community and group features
  - **profile/** - User profile components
  - **user/** - User-related components
  - **settings/** - Settings interface components
  - **discover/** - Discovery and search components
  - **navbar/** - Navigation components

- **src/hooks/** - Custom React hooks
  - **lens/** - Lens Protocol specific hooks
  - **chat/** - Chat functionality hooks
  - **community/** - Community-related hooks

- **src/lib/** - Utilities and shared code
  - **constants/** - App constants and configuration
  - **types/** - TypeScript type definitions

- **src/services/** - External service integrations

- **src/stores/** - State management with Zustand

## Configuration Files

- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration
- [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js) - TailwindCSS configuration
- [components.json](mdc:components.json) - UI component configuration
